06/04/2006
ATHENS, Greece -- Finance Minister George Alogoskoufis and Turkish Minister of State Kursad Tuzmen met in Athens on Wednesday (5 April), voicing mutual willingness to boost bilateral trade and economic ties by establishing regular co-operation.
The talks followed groundbreaking news about the National Bank of Greece's future purchase of a 46 per cent stake in Turkey's Finansbank.
(Kathimerini - 06/04/06;
TurkishPress.com, ANA - 05/04/06)
